text: Manfred Kluth (born 2 July 1936) is a West German rower who represented the United Team of Germany. He competed at the 1960 Summer Olympics in Rome with the men's coxless four where they were eliminated in the round one repêchage. ==References== Category:1936 births Category:Living people Category:West German male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of the United Team of Germany Category:Rowers at the 1960 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Düsseldorf Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
